<!-- entry -->
	<h2 class="date-header">November 19, 2007</h2>


<div class="entry" id="entry-41771318">
			<h3 class="entry-header">DLR Hosting Specs (on Silicon)</h3>
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<div class="entry-body">
			<p><a title="DLR Hosting Specification by John Lam, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/john_lam/2047711131/"><img height="375" alt="DLR Hosting Specification" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2017/2047711131_d4ce321ca9.jpg" width="500" /></a></p>

<p>We're serious about our specs here on the DLR team. Not content with just publishing specs in electronic format, we've committed them to <strong>silicon!</strong></p>

<p>Here's a <a href="http://www.iunknown.com/files/dlr-spec-hosting.pdf">PDF copy of the spec (1MB)</a> of the that we're working on over the next few months. We've done a bunch of rounds of internal review on this spec and we'd love to incorporate your feedback.</p>

<p>You can leave feedback here in the comments, or you can send mail directly to Bill Chiles (billchi) or the DLR alias (dlr) at Microsoft dot com.</p>
		</div>
		
					<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/LessIsBetter?i=http://www.iunknown.com/2007/11/dlr-hosting-spe.html" type="text/javascript"></script>
		
	</div>
	<div class="entry-footer">
					<p class="entry-footer-info">
